BY SOLOMON NDA-ISAIAH, MC Godwin Favour, a UK based gospel music minister and master of ceremony has reloaded his single, “Ajerese” in which he featured the award winning Xplicits Gospel Crew (Nig). “Ajerese” which means Strong Tower in Benin/Urobho dialect, expresses the awesomeness and how powerful our Creator Is. The song was birthed in the place of prayer and deep fellowship with the Father and was skillfully produced by Tobass Adolphus with the fusion of folk and rock. The Xplicits is a Gospel group of talented, gifted, graceful and resourceful Music Ministers (artistes) from different states in Nigeria based in the FCT, coming in unity to spread the message of Love, impact and worship of Our Lord and Saviour Jesus Christ. The group have recorded over 35 songs and have released 5 songs including an EP album which is available in shops nationwide and online stores, shot a video of “Oduwe” in Igala dialect meaning “Your Name is Wonderful” and “Okaka” in Igbo dialect meaning “Greater Than the greatest”. Currently, TXGC is putting up campus tours to promote peace and Unity. They have also featured some Nigeria and International artistes coming on their album Project. 